      ## What “domain” should mean for this plan
      Treat domain as **server-side business boundary** (not UI page), roughly:
      - auth
      - settings
      - workspace (settings/members/invites/transcripts)
      - projects
      - chat
      - billing (workspace + console catalog/admin)
      - console administration
      - assistant orchestration/tooling
      - deg2rad/history (if kept as separate capability domain)

      ## Hard requirements
      - Action definitions and handlers live with domain ownership.
      - Central action registry lives in app composition root and explicitly mounts contributors.
      - No hidden side-effect auto-registration.
      - Removing a package/domain contributor should remove its actions by composition choice.
      - Permission checks must happen in action execution path, not only routes.
      - Plan must preserve backward compatibility during migration.
      - Include strategy for assistant parity with UI capabilities using shared actions.
      - Include audit + idempotency policy recommendations for mutating actions.
      - No tables in your output.

